<!-- Bio -->
    <div class="main">
      <div class="bio" id="bio">

        <h3>About Me</h3>

        <p>Hi, I'm Emily Hann, undergraduate student at the University of Pittsburgh studying both
          anthropology and digital narrative and interactive design. This is my first website using HTML
          and CSS. I have always been interested in the interaction between humans and the digital world.
          We are constantly surrounded by digital media and the way we utilize and engage with others
          using technology is mediated by our cultural upbringing. My goal is to study how we interpret
          society, culture, and other individuals through the lens of the digital landscape. With this,
          we can continue to foster new online relationships that foster understanding, cultural exchange,
          and globalization.
        </p>

      </div>


  <!-- Education -->
      <div class="education" id="anthro">

        <h4>Anthropology</h4>

        <p>Through cross-cultural analysis and communication, I am qualified to conduct research
          that focuses on the culturally specific relationships between people, technology, and society.
          My goal is to not only to understand others and their behaviors and to describe their experiences
          accurately, but to share and build intercultural relationships that benefit both parties. In this
          way, I can approach digital design with a cultural lens that appropriately conveys information
          and enhances user experiences and interaction.
        </p>

      </div>
  <!--End Anthropology-->

      <div class="education" id="dnid">

        <h4>Digital Narrative and Interactive Design</h4>

        <p>Combining design, narrative, and coding, I am currently acquiring the hard skills required to
          produce interactive media experiences that use storytelling to convey information through human-computer
          interfaces. I have experience in programming languages Python, HTML, and CSS and editing software such
          as Audacity and Gimp, which I have used to create a variety of media for class projects. In combination
          with my anthropology degree, I hope to create rich cultural narratives through digital media that enhance
          cultural awareness and foster diversity, inclusion, and understanding within various communities.
        </p>

      </div>
  <!--End DNID-->

